				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13035011/scp-5020#post-4590490</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2020 13:56:53 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>bibliolatry</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3534136</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This article is both hilarious and creepy to me, but there's just one thing that prevents it from *really* resonating with me: of all of the consoles that I think of when it comes to ones that can be damaged by exposure, the Atari 2600 doesn't actually come to mind. It doesn't get plastic yellowing, the woodgrain isn't really that susceptible to damage, etc. Sure, it can get crudded up, but it's possible to clean up with a bit of elbow grease. When I think of rank old consoles, what usually comes to mind is those piss-yellow SNES systems that got left in the sun. Still, 1+</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
