					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13035011#post-4504855</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13035011/scp-5020#post-4504855</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 17 Feb 2020 18:48:34 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Dr Karren</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5968578</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I was personally scared when I read this because I have an Atari that meets all the requirements for SCP-5020-A to manifest. But this article was put to together very well. This article hits scary when it comes to people who have Ataris of people that have a friend who has an Atari. This article also hits comedy when it comes to the complaint letters and one of the few main list SCP that actually made me chuckle. Good SCP</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;words</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;empty</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>I don't know why, but this line made me laugh:</p> <blockquote> <p>These &quot;bugs&quot; you speak of are in fact an important feature of the Atari 2600</p> </blockquote> <p>bruh&#8230;</p> </div> </div> </div> <p><strong>+1</strong></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
